<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14499">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Digital%20Technology.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14539">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      View the
      <a href="https://www.scouting.org/training/youth-protection/scouts-bsa/"
        >Personal Safety Awareness "Digital Safety" video </a
      >(with your parent or guardian's permission).
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14500">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14500 mb-requirement-id-14501">
        (a) Give a brief history of the changes in digital technology over time.
        Discuss with your counselor how digital technology in your lifetime
        compares with that of your parent's, grandparent's, or other adult's
        lifetime. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IJM3yuIDDPQ?si=7uQQJs6mbXI7sRHF"
          target="_blank"
          >Technology Evolution - 100,000 BCE to 2020 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IKLVSxhkZeg?si=jzzto-HMQ-Xzl-MT"
          target="_blank"
          >Past &amp; Present Technology, Then &amp; Now (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DENG7Q7VRgo?si=giprDI8VZC04gldJ"
          target="_blank"
          >Past and Present | Technology Then and Now (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14500 mb-requirement-id-14502">
        (b) Describe what kinds of computers or devices you imagine might be
        available when you are an adult. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/v942xxcJWlA?si=61vZc5bgAiTD_7Oa"
          target="_blank"
          >Technologies of the Future (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14503">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14503 mb-requirement-id-14504">
        (a) Explain to your counselor how text, sound, and pictures are
        digitized for storage. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zB85kTs-sEw?si=zbhOXnxeEGM-vhAs"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is ASCII? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/pmY7pOQCOr8?si=RcB32mhzHzjhNHtM"
          target="_blank"
          >How Images and Sound are Represented in a Computer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14503 mb-requirement-id-14505">
        (b) Describe the difference between lossy and lossless data compression,
        and give an example where each might be used. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X88vxU2o4f0" target="_blank"
          >Lossy vs Lossless Data Compression (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14503 mb-requirement-id-14506">
        (c) Describe two digital devices and how they are made more useful by
        their programming. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2NpRkV1qLDY?si=ivYUBEzE_xQYi6Ka"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of Digital Devices (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14503 mb-requirement-id-14507">
        (d) Discuss the similarities and differences between computers, mobile
        devices, and gaming consoles. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/UdkG0NZTJak" target="_blank"
          >Comparing PC to Gaming Consoles. (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://techousegames.com/mobile-vs-pc-vs-console-gaming/"
          target="_blank"
          >Mobile vs Pc vs Console Gaming (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14503 mb-requirement-id-14508">
        (e) Explain what a computer network is and the difference between a
        local area network (LAN) versus a wide area network (WAN). <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aHJElrgj6UA" target="_blank"
          >Difference Between LAN and WAN (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14509">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14509 mb-requirement-id-14510">
        (a) Explain what a program or software application or "app" is and how a
        computer uses a CPU and memory to execute it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DKGZlaPlVLY" target="_blank"
          >How Computers Work (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/3gMOYZoMtEs?si=bVq_MqhT-LMeDH1E"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is an App? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/p3q5zWCw8J4?si=6qaC9vmHQDuMQjWW"
          target="_blank"
          >How Computer Memory Works (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14509 mb-requirement-id-14511">
        (b) Name four software programs or mobile apps you or your family use,
        and explain how each one helps you. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3gMOYZoMtEs" target="_blank"
          >Understandng Software Applications (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14509 mb-requirement-id-14512">
        (c) Describe what malware is, and explain how to protect your digital
        devices and the information stored on them. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NMYbkzjI5EY" target="_blank"
          >What Is Malware? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14509 mb-requirement-id-14540">
        (d) Explain what a barcode, a QR code, and an RFID tag are along with
        the data they contain and two or more examples where each are used.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14513">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14513 mb-requirement-id-14514">
        (a) Describe at least two different ways data can be transferred through
        the internet. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ge05p3GV3SI?si=ZnZmRf_R6RICJ4Ed"
          target="_blank"
          >How the Internet ACTUALLY Works ? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtube.com/shorts/lylaitbZB70?si=Jq_-Z0aSSn6gvok4"
          target="_blank"
          >This Is How Data Is Transferred in the Internet (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kZTF7wIykk4?si=u-zUEl43v9dBXRwr"
          target="_blank"
          >Data Transfer Via the Internet Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14513 mb-requirement-id-14515">
        (b) Using an internet search engine (with a parent or guardian's
        permission), find ideas from at least three different websites about how
        to conduct a troop court of honor or campfire program. Present the ideas
        to your counselor and explain how you used a search engine to find this
        information.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14513 mb-requirement-id-14516">
        (c) Use a web browser to connect to an HTTPS (secure) website (with your
        parent or guardian's permission). Explain to your counselor how to tell
        whether the site's security certificate can be trusted, and what it
        means to use this kind of connection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3j64UNXALHo" target="_blank"
          >What Is HTTPS? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14517">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do THREE of the following. For each project you complete, copy the files
      to a backup device and share the finished projects with your counselor.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14518">
        (a) Using a spreadsheet or database program, develop a food budget for a
        patrol weekend campout OR create a troop roster that includes the name,
        rank, patrol, and telephone number of each Scout. Show your counselor
        that you can sort the roster by each of the following categories: rank,
        patrol, and alphabetically by name. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VFp6Yufsg-Q" target="_blank"
          >Introduction to Spreadsheets (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14519">
        (b) Using a word processor, write a draft letter to the parents of your
        troop's Scouts, inviting them to a troop event. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lrw5t7-Tzb8" target="_blank"
          >Word Processing Tutorial (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14520">
        (c) Using a graphics program, design and draw a campsite plan for your
        troop OR create a flyer for an upcoming troop event, incorporating text
        and some type of visual such as a photograph or an illustration.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eSU0JbxWpoc?si=Ry7E0T6yO3djUivs"
          target="_blank"
          >Google Drawing Basics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14521">
        (d) Using a presentation software program, develop a report about a
        topic approved by your counselor. For your presentation, create at least
        five slides, with each one incorporating text and some type of visual
        such as a photograph or an illustration. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7vSnesQDLBE" target="_blank"
          >Google Slides for Presentations (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14522">
        (e) Using a digital device, take a picture of a troop activity. Send or
        transfer this image to a device where it can be shared with your
        counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Tc5Jmx5O1g" target="_blank"
          >Sending Photos on a Smartphone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14523">
        (f) Make a digital recording of your voice, transfer the file to a
        different device, and have your counselor play back the recording.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9x4ZtNuB1ik" target="_blank"
          >How to Make an Audio File With a Smartphone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14524">
        (g) Create a blog and use it as an online journal of your Scouting
        activities, including group discussions and meetings, campouts, and
        other events. Include at least five entries and two photographs or
        illustrations. Share your blog with your counselor. You need not post
        the blog to the internet; however, if you choose to go live with your
        blog, you must first share it with your parent or guardian AND counselor
        AND get their approval. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KkKp56E6UVo?si=KC9FQG9OrMaLMRys"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Write a Blog Post for Beginners: From Start to End (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14517 mb-requirement-id-14525">
        (h) Create a webpage for your troop, patrol, school, or place of
        worship. Include at least three articles and two photographs or
        illustrations. Include at least one link to a website of interest to
        your audience. You need not post the page to the internet; however, if
        you decide to do so, you must first share the webpage with your parent
        or guardian AND counselor AND get their approval. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BBcq9abR9Es" target="_blank"
          >How to Create a Simple Webpage (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14526">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14526 mb-requirement-id-14527">
        (a) Explain to your counselor each of these protections and why they
        exist: copyright, patents, trademarks, trade secrets. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LyQOf5bqdzo" target="_blank"
          >Explanations of Copyrights, Patents, Trademarks, Trade Secrets
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14526 mb-requirement-id-14528">
        (b) Explain when it is permissible to accept a free copy of a program
        from a friend. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DzsgYoc-qNc?si=kO8fIsXs2p7Fa7GP"
          target="_blank"
          >Digital Etiquette for Teenagers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14526 mb-requirement-id-14529">
        (c) Discuss with your counselor an article or (with your parent or
        guardian's permission) a report on the internet about a recent legal
        case involving an intellectual property dispute. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.reuters.com/legal/intellectual-property/"
          target="_blank"
          >Intellectual Property (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14530">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14530 mb-requirement-id-14531">
        (a) Describe why it is important to properly dispose of digital
        technology. List at least three hazardous chemicals that could be used
        to create digital devices or used inside a digital device. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/9ZW0AZZ_0Wg?si=xZXCX_jNjp0RTn2i"
          target="_blank"
          >What Are the Risks of Not Properly Disposing of Technology?
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/HmEhTIMfZiI?si=gG-ytCg1jxlaC3q_"
          target="_blank"
          >3 Simple Tips for Recycling Old Electronics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14530 mb-requirement-id-14532">
        (b) Explain to your counselor why it is important to use a certified
        recycler of digital technology hardware or devices. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IIM9-kBRh1A?si=WMptMoGNeXFlZHpI"
          target="_blank"
          >How to (Properly) Get Rid of Your E-Waste (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14530 mb-requirement-id-14533">
        (c) Do an internet search for an organization that collects discarded
        digital technology hardware or devices for repurposing or recycling.
        Find out what happens to that waste. Share with your counselor what you
        found. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w0ikFMTuS9c" target="_blank"
          >How E-Wastes Are Recycled (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14530 mb-requirement-id-14534">
        (d) Visit a recycling center that disposes of digital technology
        hardware or devices. Find out what happens to that waste. Share what you
        learned with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://e-stewards.org/find-a-recycler/" target="_blank"
          >Finding an E-Waste Recycler (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14530 mb-requirement-id-14535">
        (e) Find a battery recycling center near you and find out what it does
        to recycle batteries. Share what you have learned with your counselor
        about the proper methods for recycling batteries. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.recyclerfinder.com/" target="_blank"
          >Finding a Battery Recycler (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14536">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14536 mb-requirement-id-14537">
        (a) Explore careers related to the <i>Digital Technology</i> merit
        badge. Research one career to learn about the training and education
        needed, costs, job prospects, salary, job duties, and career
        advancement. Your research methods may include—with your parent or
        guardian's permission—an internet or library search, an interview with a
        professional in the field, or a visit to a location where people in this
        career work. Discuss with your counselor both your findings and what
        about this profession might make it an interesting career. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://career.albany.edu/videos/digital-technology/"
          target="_blank"
          >Digital Technology Careers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14536 mb-requirement-id-14538">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills from the
        <i>Digital Technology</i> merit badge to pursue a hobby or interest.
        Research any training needed, expenses, and organizations that promote
        or support it. Discuss with your counselor what short-term and long-term
        goals you might have if you pursued this.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
